UCT vice chancellor Max Price says the university is ready for the 2017 final year exams despite threats of protests by some student groups. CAPE TOWN - UCT vice chancellor Max Price says the university is ready for the 2017 final year exams despite threats of protests by some student groups. The university says exams are set to begin on 15 November. The last three months saw a spike in student protest over free education. Students across the province marched to Parliament demanding a zero fee increase for the 2018 academic year. UCT’s Max Price said, “At UCT we are well prepared for the exams, we have a designated venue and the exams start on Wednesday.”